      • DummyPoint

        public wPoint DummyPoint
        code 10,20,30 A "dummy" point. The X and Y coordinates are always 0, and the Z coordinate is the polyline's elevation (in OCS when 2D, WCS when 3D).

      • vtxFollow

        public int vtxFollow
        code 66 - Vertices-follow flag (always 1 for a polyline).

      • TypeFlag

        public int TypeFlag
        code 70 - Polyline flag (bit-coded); default is 0.
        • 1 = This is a closed polyline (or a polygon mesh closed in the M directtion).
        • 2 = Curve-fit vertices have been added.
        • 4 = Spline-fit vertices have been added.
        • 8 = This is a 3D polyline.
        • 16 = This is a 3D polygon mesh.
        • 32 = The polygon mesh is closed in the N direction.
        • 64 = The polyline is a polyface mesh.
        • 128 = The linetype pattern is generated continuously around the vertices of this polyline.

      • meshcntM

        public int meshcntM
        code 71 - Polygon mesh M vertex count (optional; default = 0).

      • meshcntN

        public int meshcntN
        code 72 - Polygon mesh N vertex count (optional; default = 0).

      • smoothM

        public int smoothM
        code 73 - Smooth surface M density (optional; default = 0).

      • smoothN

        public int smoothN
        code 74 - Smooth surface N density (optional; default = 0).

      • surfType

        public int surfType
        code 75 - Curves and smooth surface type (optional; default = 0).
        • 0 = No smooth surface fitted.
        • 5 = Quadratic B-spline surface.
        • 6 = Cubic B-spline surface.
        • 8 = Bezier surface.

      • xExtrusionDirection

        public double xExtrusionDirection
        code 210,220,230 - Extrusion direction. Present if the extrusion direction is not parallel to the world Z axis.

      • yExtrusionDirection

        public double yExtrusionDirection
